text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia mooreana is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area along the south coast in the South West and Great Southern regions of Western Australia.The erect, slender and pungent shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 1 metre (0.7 to 3.3 ft). It blooms from May to September and produces yellow-cream flowers.
